    <caption>The oceans are not simply
    <q>concentrated</q>
    river water. Rivers are the primary, but not only, factor contribution to the ocean's salinity. rivers (in the blue shading) and oceans (in pink) have distinctly different ratios of ions. If the oceans were simply concetrated river water, the proportions of ions in each would be identical. As the graph shows, this is not true. Other sources and sinks<mdash/>which reside in the Geosphere and Biosphere<mdash/>must modify sea water's composition.</caption>
